title: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Leeds United have lost nine of their last 11 Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, including each of their last four in a row – their longest ever league losing run to Spurs. Tottenham have won both of their last two league visits to Elland Road and could beat Leeds United away from home three times running in the league for the very first time.

title: Latvia vs England - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
title_en_trans: Latvia vs England - UEFA European Qualifiers World Cup 2026 - MD8
synopsis: This will be the second meeting between Latvia and England, with the first coming in March this year when the Three Lions won 3-0 at Wembley with goals from Reece James, Harry Kane and Eberechi Eze. Latvia will be the 72nd nation England have played an away match against – they’ve won their last three first time away games against a nation.

title: Nikoloz BASILASHVILI (GEO) vs Giovanni MPETSHI PERRICARD (FRA) - ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brus
title_en_trans: Nikoloz BASILASHVILI (GEO) vs Giovanni MPETSHI PERRICARD (FRA) - ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brus
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Gold Standard Ep6
synopsis:
"A Farewell to Legends" – France 2017
France’s 2017 victory on home soil was both a celebration and a goodbye to legends like Omeyer and Narcisse. 
This emotional win against Norway secured their sixth title and closed a golden chapter in French handball.

title_en_trans: Damir DZUMHUR (BIH) vs Felix AUGER-ALIASSIME (CAN) - ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: My Faith in Sport - Sawm
synopsis: Ramadan is a crucial period in the Islamic calendar but fasting (Sawm) can provide complications for athletes who are trying to compete at the highest level. But to what extent is fasting a negative or can it actually aid performance? We look at the life and adaptation throughout Ramadan of Adam Azim – an unbeaten professional boxer from the UK, Fares El Bakh – a weightlifter who won Qatar’s first ever Olympic gold medal, and Zainab Alema – a rugby player who is aiming to become the first player to represent England wearing a hijab. Experts in Sports Science and Nutrition from Aspetar Clinic, Qatar also add detail of the physical impact athletes encounter during Ramadan.

synopsis: Scotland have won three of their previous five meetings with Belarus, with each of those coming in World Cup qualifying – the most recent was just last month, with the Scots winning 2-0 in Belarus. This will be Belarus’ third trip to face Scotland, losing the first 4-1 in September 1997 before winning the most recent 1-0 in October 2005.

synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. synopsis:
The AFC Champions League Two is the second-tier competition of Asian club football, ranked below the AFC Champions League Elite. 
Participation in the competition is open to clubs from the top 12 nations in the East and the West region based on the AFC club competitions ranking.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Olympique Lyonnais vs Toulouse - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
title_en_trans: Olympique Lyonnais vs Toulouse - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Olympique Lyonnais are unbeaten in their last 17 Ligue 1 matches against Toulouse FC, a longer run in the top-flight has only been recorded against Saint-Étienne. Olympique Lyonnais have conceded just three goals in Ligue 1 this season, the joint-lowest tally in the league alongside Nice, and their fewest after six matches of a top-flight campaign since 2015/16.

title: Botic VAN DE ZANDSCHULP (NED) vs Eliot SPIZZIRRI (USA) - ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
title_en_trans: Botic VAN DE ZANDSCHULP (NED) vs Eliot SPIZZIRRI (USA) - ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Leeds United vs Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Leeds United vs Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Leeds United have lost nine of their last 11 Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, including each of their last four in a row – their longest ever league losing run to Spurs. synopsis: World No.1 pairing Gemma Triay/Delfina Brea face No.2 Ariana Sánchez/Paula Josemaría at Rotterdam Ahoy. A classic rivalry: Triay/Brea lead the season with multiple titles, including Germany P2 last week, while Sánchez/Josemaría chase revenge after losing six of seven meetings this year. Expect sharp returns, low volleys, and golden-point pressure in a battle for supremacy.

title: Al Hilal SFC (KSA) vs Al Duhail SC (QAT) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
title_en_trans: Al Hilal SFC (KSA) vs Al Duhail SC (QAT) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
synopsis: Al Duhail won their first AFC Champions League Elite meeting with Al-Hilal, but Al-Hilal are unbeaten in the six since, including their joint-biggest win in the competition  – Al Duhail’s heaviest defeat in the tournament. Qatari teams have lost their last five matches against Saudi sides in the competition; their last win was Al Sadd’s 2-1 victory over Al-Nassr in December 2014. Qatari teams have lost more matches  and conceded more goals  against Saudi teams than against any other nation.

synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. title: Arturo Coello (ESP) / Agustin Tapia (ARG) vs  Federico Chingotto (ARG) / Alejandro Galan (ESP) - Men
title_en_trans: Arturo Coello (ESP) / Agustin Tapia (ARG) vs  Federico Chingotto (ARG) / Alejandro Galan (ESP) - Men
synopsis: Top seeds Arturo Coello/Agustín Tapia clash with No.2 Alejandro Galán/Federico Chingotto. Coello/Tapia dominated most of 2025, but Galán/Chingotto struck back with victory in Germany P2. Head-to-head favors Coello/Tapia, yet momentum is split after recent meetings. Indoor conditions at Rotterdam Ahoy amplify aggressive volleys and x-3 smashes, setting up a high-stakes P1 decider.

synopsis: This will be the second meeting between Latvia and England, with the first coming in March this year when the Three Lions won 3-0 at Wembley with goals from Reece James, Harry Kane and Eberechi Eze. title: Damir DZUMHUR (BIH) vs Felix AUGER-ALIASSIME (CAN) - ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
title_en_trans: Damir DZUMHUR (BIH) vs Felix AUGER-ALIASSIME (CAN) - ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3 - Mini Match
title_en_trans: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3 - Mini Match
synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Leeds United have lost nine of their last 11 Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, including each of their last four in a row – their longest ever league losing run to Spurs. Tottenham have won both of their last two league visits to Elland Road and could beat Leeds United away from home three times running in the league for the very first time.

synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Manchester United vs Sunderland - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Manchester United vs Sunderland - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Manchester United have lost just two of their last 30 league games against Sunderland, with this their first since a 3-0 win in April 2017. Across all competitions, Sunderland have managed to win just one of their last 31 away games against Manchester United, winning 1-0 in May 2014 thanks to Sebastian Larsson’s winner.

synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: One Friday Fight -129
synopsis: ONE Friday Fights 129 lights up Bangkok on Oct 17 with 12 bouts across Muay Thai, MMA, and kickboxing. Expect fireworks in the headliner as Thailand’s Tengnueng collides with Myanmar’s Tun Min Aung in a KO-hungry showdown. Plus, standout clashes: Petlampun vs Ayad Albadr, and 19-year-old Fergus Smith vs Zahran Al-Wesabi. Live from Lumpinee Boxing Stadium, its elbows, knees, and spinning kicks all night in a stacked showcase. Prelims spotlight rising prospects; main card promises fast finishes.

High skills, passion for technology, impatience for innovation, and pure love for adrenaline, are combined at their best. So, start your engines, tighten your seat belts, and get ready to feel the G-force with some serious action!

title: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
title_en_trans: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Lille have won just one of their last 13 home Ligue 1 games against Paris SG, a 5-1 victory on 14 April 2019, which remains Paris Saint-Germain's biggest away defeat in the top-flight in the 21st century. Lille have lost their last two Ligue 1 matches and could suffer three consecutive defeats in the competition for the first time since December 2019-January 2020. Lille could also fail to score in three consecutive Ligue 1 games for the first time since September 2017.

synopsis: The Qatari League is the official football league in Qatar. The league includes 12 teams. The most famous participating clubs are Al-Sadd, the champions of the last season; Al-Rayyan and Al-Arabi, the popular teams, Al-Duhail and Al-Gharafa, serious contenders for the title every season. title: Brentford vs. Manchester City - English Premier League 2025/2026

title: M2 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

synopsis: The Qatari League is the official football league in Qatar. The league includes 12 teams. The most famous participating clubs are Al-Sadd, the champions of the last season; Al-Rayyan and Al-Arabi, the popular teams, Al-Duhail and Al-Gharafa, serious contenders for the title every season. synopsis: This will be the second meeting between Latvia and England, with the first coming in March this year when the Three Lions won 3-0 at Wembley with goals from Reece James, Harry Kane and Eberechi Eze. title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

synopsis: Paris Saint-Germain are unbeaten in their 34 home games against Strasbourg in Ligue 1, the most home games by a team against another without losing in the history of the top-flight. Paris Saint-Germain have won three Ligue 1 matches by two or more goals this season, the joint-most with Marseille, though they have only done so fewer times after seven Ligue 1 matches in two previous seasons under QSI ownership.

synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

synopsis: Real Madrid have not lost any of their last four LaLiga games against Villarreal, winning the last two, this after failing to win any of their previous four against the Yellows in the competition. They have not won three or more in a row against them in LaLiga since 2011. Villarreal have lost 17 of their 25 LaLiga away matches against Real Madrid, their highest number of away defeats against a single opponent in the competition.

title: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
title_en_trans: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
synopsis: WorldSBK heads to Estoril for the weekend’s decisive Race 2. The long front straight and technical infield reward grip and bravery, with braking into Parabólica and the drag to Turn 1 often settling it. Expect drafting trains, tyre-management gambles, and late lunges as title hopes to tighten in a full-throttle finale.

synopsis: This will be the first time Sanfrecce Hiroshima and Shanghai Port face off in the AFC Champions League Elite; Sanfrecce Hiroshima have won just two of their 10 games against opponents from China in the competition, with a win in their most recent such game. title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Arsenal vs West Ham United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8

synopsis: Arsenal have lost both of their last two home league games against West Ham, only ever losing three in a row once before. West Ham United are looking to become only the second side to win three successive Premier League away games against Arsenal, after Manchester City, who won six on the bounce from March 2018 to February 2023.

title: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
title_en_trans: Race 2 - World Super Bike - Estoril Round 2025
synopsis: WorldSBK heads to Estoril for the weekend’s decisive Race 2. The long front straight and technical infield reward grip and bravery, with braking into Parabólica and the drag to Turn 1 often settling it. Expect drafting trains, tyre-management gambles, and late lunges as title hopes to tighten in a full-throttle finale.

synopsis: This will be the first time Sanfrecce Hiroshima and Shanghai Port face off in the AFC Champions League Elite; Sanfrecce Hiroshima have won just two of their 10 games against opponents from China in the competition, with a win in their most recent such game. title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Arsenal vs West Ham United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8

synopsis: Arsenal have lost both of their last two home league games against West Ham, only ever losing three in a row once before. West Ham United are looking to become only the second side to win three successive Premier League away games against Arsenal, after Manchester City, who won six on the bounce from March 2018 to February 2023.

title: PSG vs Strasbourg - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: PSG vs Strasbourg - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Paris Saint-Germain are unbeaten in their 34 home games against Strasbourg in Ligue 1, the most home games by a team against another without losing in the history of the top-flight. Paris Saint-Germain have won three Ligue 1 matches by two or more goals this season, the joint-most with Marseille, though they have only done so fewer times after seven Ligue 1 matches in two previous seasons under QSI ownership.

title: Al Arabi vs Umm Salal - Qatar Stars League 2025/26 - W3
title_en_trans: Al Arabi vs Umm Salal - Qatar Stars League 2025/26 - W3
synopsis: The Qatari League is the official football league in Qatar. The league includes 12 teams. The most famous participating clubs are Al-Sadd, the champions of the last season; Al-Rayyan and Al-Arabi, the popular teams, Al-Duhail and Al-Gharafa, serious contenders for the title every season. The Qatari league includes star names such as Firmino, Verratti, and Qatari Akram Afif, the best player in Asia.

title: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Leeds United vs. Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Leeds United have lost nine of their last 11 Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, including each of their last four in a row – their longest ever league losing run to Spurs. Tottenham have won both of their last two league visits to Elland Road and could beat Leeds United away from home three times running in the league for the very first time.

synopsis: The two previous meetings between Napoli and Sporting CP have both finished 0-0, with both coming in the first round of the 1989-90 UEFA Cup first round. Napoli have won all four of their UEFA Champions League matches against Portuguese sides, beating Benfica twice in 2016-17 and Braga twice in 2023-24.

title: M2 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title_en_trans: Al Gharafa SC (QAT) vs Al Shorta (IRQ) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD2
synopsis: This will be the first meeting between Al Gharafa and Al Shorta in the AFC Champions League Elite; Al Gharafa is winless in their two encounters against Iraqi sides in the competition  while Al Shorta is unbeaten in their last two games against Qatari sides. Al Gharafa won their most recent home game in the AFC Champions League Elite, the last time they won back-to-back home games in the competition was a run of three games between May 2012 and April 2013; they kept a clean sheet in their previous home game, they have never recorded back-to-back clean sheets at home in the competition.

Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Sanfrecce Hiroshima (JPN) vs Shanghai Port FC (CHN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD
title_en_trans: Sanfrecce Hiroshima (JPN) vs Shanghai Port FC (CHN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD
synopsis: This will be the first time Sanfrecce Hiroshima and Shanghai Port face off in the AFC Champions League Elite; Sanfrecce Hiroshima have won just two of their 10 games against opponents from China in the competition, with a win in their most recent such game. Shanghai Port are currently on a five-game losing streak in the AFC Champions League Elite, last registering a win on 26 November 2024 ; in fact, they have lost each of their last seven games in the competition against opponents from Japan.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Chelsea vs Benfica - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs Benfica - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
synopsis: Chelsea have won all four of their competitive meetings with Benfica, with the most recent of those coming earlier this year at the FIFA Club World Cup. This will be the first meeting between Chelsea and Benfica in the group/league phase of a competition, with the previous four all having come in the knockout stages: UEFA Champions League quarter-finals in 2011-12, UEFA Europa League final in 2012-13 and the FIFA Club World Cup last 16 earlier this year.

title: M2 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title_en_trans: AFC Bournemouth vs Fulham - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Bournemouth have lost just two of their last 16 league meetings with Fulham, and just one of their last eight, going down 3-1 in February 2024. title: M3 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. title: Brentford vs. Manchester City - English Premier League 2025/2026

description_en_trans: Nice have lost each of their last three Ligue 1 matches against Lyon, as many as in their previous 11. The Aiglons could suffer four consecutive defeats against OL in the top flight for the first time since March 2003-August 2004. Nice have conceded 12 goals after seven Ligue 1 matches in 2025/26, having conceded more at this stage of a Ligue 1 season only once in the last 40 years.

synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: M2 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

title: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

synopsis: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton  since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Only against Fulham, West Brom, and West Ham  are the Citizens currently on a longer unbeaten run in the competition. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. title: Nottingham Forest vs Chelsea - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8

synopsis: Nottingham Forest have won just one of their last eight Premier League meetings with Chelsea, a 1-0 victory at Stamford Bridge in September 2023. The Blues have never before won three successive away league games against the Tricky Trees.

title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. title_en_trans: Chengdu Rongcheng FC vs Gangwon FC (KOR) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD2
synopsis: Chengdu Rongcheng will face Gangwon for the first time in AFC Champions League Elite; each of the last three games in the competition between teams from Korea and China have been won by the former by an exact 2-1 score, including Gangwon’s win over Shanghai Shenhua in the first round of the 2025-26 season. Gangwon beat Shanghai Shenhua 2-1 in their first ever AFC Champions League Elite game at home; the last Korean side to suffer at least one defeat in their first two games in the competition is Jeju United in 2011, while no side from Korea has suffered defeat in their first away game in the AFC Champions League Elite.

title_en_trans: Crystal Palace vs AFC Bournemouth - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Crystal Palace have failed to score in each of their last four Premier League games against Bournemouth. The only side the Eagles have ever gone 5+ consecutive games without a goal against in the competition are Tottenham Hotspur. Both Premier League meetings between Bournemouth and Crystal Palace last season finished goalless; in the competition’s history, the only fixtures to see three consecutive 0-0 draws are Arsenal v QPR, Aston Villa v Man Utd, Coventry v Sheffield Wednesday, and Charlton v Middlesbrough.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026

synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. title: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

synopsis: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton  since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Only against Fulham, West Brom, and West Ham  are the Citizens currently on a longer unbeaten run in the competition. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea  have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title_en_trans: Crystal Palace vs AFC Bournemouth - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Crystal Palace have failed to score in each of their last four Premier League games against Bournemouth. The only side the Eagles have ever gone 5+ consecutive games without a goal against in the competition are Tottenham Hotspur. Both Premier League meetings between Bournemouth and Crystal Palace last season finished goalless; in the competition’s history, the only fixtures to see three consecutive 0-0 draws are Arsenal v QPR, Aston Villa v Man Utd, Coventry v Sheffield Wednesday, and Charlton v Middlesbrough.

title: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3 - Mini Match
title_en_trans: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3 - Mini Match
synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Tractor FC (IRN) vs Al Wahda FC (UAE) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD2
title_en_trans: Tractor FC (IRN) vs Al Wahda FC (UAE) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD2
synopsis: This will be the first ever AFC Champions League Elite fixture between Tractor and Al Wahda; Tractor are unbeaten in home games against sides from UAE in the competition, while Al Wahda are winless in away matches against sides from Iran in the tournament. Al Wahda won their opening game of an AFC Champions League Elite campaign for the first time since 2007, beating Al-Ittihad 2-1 on the opening matchday of the 2025-26 season; the only other time they won their first two matches of an AFC Champions League Elite campaign was also in 2007.

title: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Celta de Vigo vs Real Sociedad - Spanish LaLiga 2025/26 - Week 9
title_en_trans: Celta de Vigo vs Real Sociedad - Spanish LaLiga 2025/26 - Week 9
synopsis: Celta de Vigo have won their last two LaLiga matches against Real Sociedad without conceding a goal, having failed to win any of their previous eight against the San Sebastian side in the competition, and have only won three in a row in the competition against them on two occasions: W3 between 1994 and 1995 and W3 between 1999 and 2000. Since the 2006/07 season, Real Sociedad have scored in 11 of their 14 LaLiga away games against Celta de Vigo, only scoring more times away to Valencia in this period.

title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Draw sizes: 28-player singles / 16-team doubles. Prize money: €706,850. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Toulouse vs Metz - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Toulouse vs Metz - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Toulouse have won 64% of their home matches against Metz in Ligue 1, their highest winning ratio against any opponent they have hosted at least 20 times in the top-flight. Toulouse's matches have produced 23 goals in Ligue 1 2025/26, the highest tally for TFC after seven matches in a Ligue 1 season since 1985/86.

title: Liverpool vs Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

title: PALESTINE, ONE JERSEY, MANY ROOTS
synopsis: Story of the Palestinian national football team, a team that is far more than the sum of its players. Separated by borders, by checkpoints, and exile, the tells is inspiring “One Jersey…Many Roots” them is a single jersey, a shared dream, and a deep sense of responsibility to players come from every corner of Palestine and from communities scattered across the globe. What unites represent their people on and off the pitch that Palestine endures. This is not just in every match, they carry not just a ball but the weight of history, identity and hope. synopsis: Nottingham Forest have won just one of their last eight Premier League meetings with Chelsea, a 1-0 victory at Stamford Bridge in September 2023. Chelsea have won three of their last four Premier League away games against Nottingham Forest, including both of their last two in a row. The Blues have never before won three successive away league games against the Tricky Trees.

synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Liverpool vs Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8

synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

title: Chartres vs PSG - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Chartres vs PSG - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

synopsis: The 2025–26 UEFA Europa League is the secondary club football tournament organised by UEFA. This is the second season played under a new format, which replaced the 32-team group stage with a 36-team league phase. Tottenham Hotspur are the reigning champions. The final will be played on 20 May 2026 at Beşiktaş Stadium in Istanbul, Turkey.

title: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Tottenham Hotspur vs Aston Villa - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Tottenham Hotspur vs Aston Villa - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: None of the last 20 Premier League matches between Tottenham Hotspur and Aston Villa have been drawn  since a 1-1 stalemate in May 2012. Only two fixtures in the competition’s history have ever had more successive games without a draw: Newcastle v Spurs  and Chelsea v Crystal Palace. Aston Villa have won four of their last six Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, as many as their previous 29 beforehand.

title: Brighton & Hove Albion vs Newcastle United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Brighton & Hove Albion vs Newcastle United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Brighton have never lost in eight Premier League home games against Newcastle United. Indeed, the Magpies are the only side to visit Brighton 5+ times in the competition without ever winning. title: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: M1 -ATP 250 - European open 2025 - Brussels
synopsis: ATP 250 European Open 2025 (10th edition) debuts in Brussels after nine years in Antwerp, staged on indoor-hard courts at Brussels Expo (Palais 12), 13–19 Oct. Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

Expect fast, first-strike tennis, sharp returns and tie-break pressure as contenders fight for late-season ranking points and momentum toward Turin.

synopsis: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton  since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Only against Fulham, West Brom, and West Ham  are the Citizens currently on a longer unbeaten run in the competition. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea  have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

title: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Crystal Palace vs AFC Bournemouth - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Crystal Palace vs AFC Bournemouth - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Crystal Palace have failed to score in each of their last four Premier League games against Bournemouth. The only side the Eagles have ever gone 5+ consecutive games without a goal against in the competition are Tottenham Hotspur. Both Premier League meetings between Bournemouth and Crystal Palace last season finished goalless; in the competition’s history, the only fixtures to see three consecutive 0-0 draws are Arsenal v QPR, Aston Villa v Man Utd, Coventry v Sheffield Wednesday, and Charlton v Middlesbrough.

title: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton  since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Only against Fulham, West Brom, and West Ham  are the Citizens currently on a longer unbeaten run in the competition. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea  have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

title: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

synopsis: Paris Saint-Germain are unbeaten in their 34 home games against Strasbourg in Ligue 1, the most home games by a team against another without losing in the history of the top-flight. Paris Saint-Germain have won three Ligue 1 matches by two or more goals this season, the joint-most with Marseille, though they have only done so fewer times after seven Ligue 1 matches in two previous seasons under QSI ownership.

title: Liverpool vs Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

title: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

title: Chartres vs PSG - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Chartres vs PSG - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Celta de Vigo vs Real Sociedad - Spanish LaLiga 2025/26 - Week 9
title_en_trans: Celta de Vigo vs Real Sociedad - Spanish LaLiga 2025/26 - Week 9
synopsis: Celta de Vigo have won their last two LaLiga matches against Real Sociedad without conceding a goal, having failed to win any of their previous eight against the San Sebastian side in the competition, and have only won three in a row in the competition against them on two occasions: W3 between 1994 and 1995 and W3 between 1999 and 2000. Since the 2006/07 season, Real Sociedad have scored in 11 of their 14 LaLiga away games against Celta de Vigo, only scoring more times away to Valencia in this period.

synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Nancy vs Amiens - French Ligue 2 - 2025/2026
synopsis: Ligue 2 is the second division of French football. Ligue 2 is contested by 18 clubs, the league operates on a system of promotion and relegation with both Ligue 1 and the third division Championnat National. The teams play 34 games each, totaling 306 games in the season. The biggest games from each match Day are live and exclusive on beIN.

title: Liverpool vs Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

title: Nice vs Olympique Lyonnais - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Nice vs Olympique Lyonnais - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Nice have lost each of their last three Ligue 1 matches against Lyon, as many as in their previous 11. The Aiglons could suffer four consecutive defeats against OL in the top flight for the first time since March 2003-August 2004. Nice have conceded 12 goals after seven Ligue 1 matches in 2025/26, having conceded more at this stage of a Ligue 1 season only once in the last 40 years.

title: Crystal Palace vs AFC Bournemouth - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Crystal Palace vs AFC Bournemouth - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Crystal Palace have failed to score in each of their last four Premier League games against Bournemouth. The only side the Eagles have ever gone 5+ consecutive games without a goal against in the competition are Tottenham Hotspur. Both Premier League meetings between Bournemouth and Crystal Palace last season finished goalless; in the competition’s history, the only fixtures to see three consecutive 0-0 draws are Arsenal v QPR, Aston Villa v Man Utd, Coventry v Sheffield Wednesday, and Charlton v Middlesbrough.

title: Toulouse vs Metz - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Toulouse vs Metz - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Toulouse have won 64% of their home matches against Metz in Ligue 1, their highest winning ratio against any opponent they have hosted at least 20 times in the top-flight. Toulouse's matches have produced 23 goals in Ligue 1 2025/26, the highest tally for TFC after seven matches in a Ligue 1 season since 1985/86.

title: EPL Stories 2025/26 - Ep.15 Edwin Van Der Sar
title_en_trans: EPL Stories 2025/26 - Ep.15 Edwin Van Der Sar
synopsis: Edwin van der Sar has faced down pressure on the biggest stages in world football, but his toughest battle came after retirement. In 2023, the legendary goalkeeper suffered a life-threatening brain haemorrhage. In this episode Edwin opens up on his recovery and looks back on his career at the top that redefined goalkeeping.

title: Chartres vs PSG - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Chartres vs PSG - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

title: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton  since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Only against Fulham, West Brom, and West Ham  are the Citizens currently on a longer unbeaten run in the competition. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea  have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

title: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Liverpool vs Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

title: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

synopsis: Top seeds Arturo Coello/Agustín Tapia clash with No.2 Alejandro Galán/Federico Chingotto. Coello/Tapia dominated most of 2025, but Galán/Chingotto struck back with victory in Germany P2. title_en_trans: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

title: PALESTINE, ONE JERSEY, MANY ROOTS
synopsis: Story of the Palestinian national football team, a team that is far more than the sum of its players. Separated by borders, by checkpoints, and exile, the tells is inspiring “One Jersey…Many Roots” them is a single jersey, a shared dream, and a deep sense of responsibility to players come from every corner of Palestine and from communities scattered across the globe. What unites represent their people on and off the pitch that Palestine endures. This is not just in every match, they carry not just a ball but the weight of history, identity and hope. Fot their supporters, each goal is a voice, each victory a declaration. Football it s a living emblem of unity, resilience and the unbreakable b

Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

synopsis: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton  since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Only against Fulham, West Brom, and West Ham  are the Citizens currently on a longer unbeaten run in the competition. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea  have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

title: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
title_en_trans: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

title: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Tottenham Hotspur vs Aston Villa - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Tottenham Hotspur vs Aston Villa - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: None of the last 20 Premier League matches between Tottenham Hotspur and Aston Villa have been drawn  since a 1-1 stalemate in May 2012. Only two fixtures in the competition’s history have ever had more successive games without a draw: Newcastle v Spurs  and Chelsea v Crystal Palace. Aston Villa have won four of their last six Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, as many as their previous 29 beforehand.

title_en_trans: Getafe vs Real Madrid - Spanish LaLiga 2025/26 - Week 9 - Mini Match
synopsis: Getafe have lost their last seven LaLiga matches against Real Madrid, failing to score in six of them, after having scored in their previous two against the Whites in the competition without conceding a goal. title: PSG vs Strasbourg - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: PSG vs Strasbourg - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Paris Saint-Germain are unbeaten in their 34 home games against Strasbourg in Ligue 1, the most home games by a team against another without losing in the history of the top-flight. Paris Saint-Germain have won three Ligue 1 matches by two or more goals this season, the joint-most with Marseille, though they have only done so fewer times after seven Ligue 1 matches in two previous seasons under QSI ownership.

title: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

title: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3 - Mini Match
title_en_trans: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3 - Mini Match
synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

title: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton  since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Only against Fulham, West Brom, and West Ham  are the Citizens currently on a longer unbeaten run in the competition. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City  since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea  have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

title: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Tremblay vs Aix - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Tremblay vs Aix - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

title: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: Chartres vs PSG - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Chartres vs PSG - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Fulham vs. Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

title: PALESTINE, ONE JERSEY, MANY ROOTS
synopsis: Story of the Palestinian national football team, a team that is far more than the sum of its players. Separated by borders, by checkpoints, and exile, the tells is inspiring “One Jersey…Many Roots” them is a single jersey, a shared dream, and a deep sense of responsibility to players come from every corner of Palestine and from communities scattered across the globe. What unites represent their people on and off the pitch that Palestine endures. This is not just in every match, they carry not just a ball but the weight of history, identity and hope. Fot their supporters, each goal is a voice, each victory a declaration. Football it s a living emblem of unity, resilience and the unbreakable b

title: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Liverpool vs. Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Indeed, since the start of 2018-19, this is the fewest defeats any side to face the Red Devils 3+ times in the competition has had against them. Manchester United are winless in their last nine Premier League games at Anfield since a 1-0 win in January 2016 under Louis van Gaal. Liverpool could become just the second side to avoid defeat in 10+ successive Premier League home games against the Red Devils, after Chelsea.

synopsis: Getafe have lost their last seven LaLiga matches against Real Madrid, failing to score in six of them, after having scored in their previous two against the Whites in the competition without conceding a goal.
